Project on Lookup Functions & Pivot Tables

Overview

This project demonstrates the use of Microsoft Excel's Lookup Functions and Pivot Tables to answer business questions from a sales dataset. The analysis focuses on extracting insights, summarizing key metrics, and transforming raw data into actionable information.

Skills Demonstrated

- Data Analysis in Microsoft Excel
- Lookup Functions (VLOOKUP/XLOOKUP)
- Pivot Table Creation and Analysis
- Data Summarization and Reporting
- Business Insight Generation

Project Highlights

- Identified customer-specific order quantities using lookup functions.
- Analyzed sales performance across different order priorities.
- Filtered and evaluated sales data by year.
- Assessed regional profitability.
- Determined the customer segment with the highest sales contribution.

Tools Used

- Microsoft Excel
- Lookup Functions
- Pivot Tables

Outcome

Successfully transformed raw sales data into meaningful insights, showcasing practical Excel skills commonly used in business intelligence and data analytics workflows.
